</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3E8F8E59FFA65F172187B3CD51A37DF8" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2AC5B4CC8DAFD340AACACAED591EE8A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C04C56575F5A76C258ECE46A1A5B0031" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
This species can be easily distinguished from other members of sect. 
<taxonomicName id="E90234EB553B978A755CFBE2A2579C78" authority="Huernia" authorityName="Bruyns, 2017 (R.Br.)" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asclepiadaceae" genus="Huernia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Huernia" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Huernia">Huernia Huernia</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="873A489E5CE00003605BD9B57DD30D7D" name="Saudi Arabia">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by the small maroon bowl-shaped flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="630CC028724F3CD17FB10331F11961F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="53CC982EDBD6FA9A693C5485E8220A87" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9FBA5DF47DB00220A3F83AF62BB64A4C" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Macrocarpus (Greek) 'makros', large; and 'karpos', fruit (
<bibRefCitation id="0C39E57CA36A08C1F6FD9CE3B4C38DD5" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-07125-0" author="Eggli, U" journalOrPublisher="Springer Science &amp; Business Media, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" refId="B19" refString="Eggli, U, Newton, LE, 2004. Etymological Dictionary of Succulent Plant Names. Springer Science &amp; Business Media, Berlin, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-07125-0" title="Etymological Dictionary of Succulent Plant Names." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-07125-0" year="2004">Eggli and Newton 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="051C8BCEC837A00C168A053FF0773473" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="preliminary conservation status">
<paragraph id="DC1D58B4F82B3ECF294B72E2EBEE9F0A" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Preliminary conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB388EC61E79DB0F5EDAB4ABB617330A" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
The species is known only from one location near Sawda Mountain; the estimated EOO and AOO of 
<quantity id="689DF56B1BF7A76F826D2D5A5F452A28" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" unit="km" value="8.0">8 km</quantity>
2 would place the species in the Critically Endangered (
<collectionCode id="E62E7CB56CA527177454A50778224480" country="Costa Rica" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15652" name="Museo Nacional de Costa Rica" type="Herbarium">CR</collectionCode>
) status. However, little is known about the size of the population and possible threats. Therefore, Data Deficient (
<collectionCode id="A59EA5CA9690536CA9770896E045148D" country="India" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13033" name="Forest Research Institute, Indian Council of Forestry Research and Education" type="Herbarium">DD</collectionCode>
) is assigned to this species.
</paragraph>
